def: False or deceitful dealing. See Double dealing, under Dealing.Shak.

An order of cephalopods which includes those with two gills, anapparatus for emitting an inky fluid, and either eight or tencephalic arms bearing suckers or hooks, as the octopi and squids. SeeCephalopoda.

One who reclaims; one who cries out against or contradicts.
One of the followers of Quesnay of France, who, in the 18thcentury, founded a system of political economy based upon thesupremacy of natural order. F. A. Walker.-- Phys`i*o*crat"ic, a.
